public class WeatherSystem {
    private boolean isCloudy;
    private int temperature;

    public WeatherSystem(boolean isCloudy, int temperature) {
        this.isCloudy = isCloudy;
        this.temperature = temperature;
    }

    public boolean willItRain() {
        if (isCloudy && temperature < 20) {
            return true;
        } else {
            return false;
        }
    }

    public void applyColdFront() {
        temperature -= 5;
    }
}",

If we apply the applyColdFront() method and subsequently willItRain() returns true, can we infer the day was not cloudy before applying the method?
